Class ImagingObjectSelection

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hl7.fhir.instance.model.Base
      • org.hl7.fhir.instance.model.BaseResource
        • org.hl7.fhir.instance.model.Resource
          • org.hl7.fhir.instance.model.DomainResource
            • org.hl7.fhir.instance.model.ImagingObjectSelection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, IAnyResource, IBase, IBaseHasExtensions, IBaseHasModifierExtensions, IBaseResource, IDomainResource

    public class ImagingObjectSelection
extends DomainResource
    A set of DICOM SOP Instances of a patient, selected for some application purpose, e.g., quality assurance, teaching, conference, consulting, etc. Objects selected can be from different studies, but must be of the same patient.

      • getAuthor

        public Reference getAuthor()

        author (Author of key object selection. It can be a human authtor or a device which made the decision of the SOP instances selected. For example, a radiologist selected a set of imaging SOP instances to attached in a diagnostic report, and a CAD application may author a selection to describe SOP instances it used to generate a detection conclusion.)
